data.title: brunch
data.text: Popular place Saturday morning.  We waited for about 30 min for a table for 6.  Very helpful staff and prompt service.  Lots of smiles, suggestions, and upbeat server.  We would definitely come back on our next trip.

data.title: Bcdc
data.text:
Both breakfast and lunch menus are awesome!  The breakfast menu has excellent egg dishes and skillets, and the lunch menu has many sandwiches and burgers.
The staff is always nice and friendly too!

data.title: Friendliest breakfast crew anywhere!
data.text: What a nice treat to go in for breakfast and have everyone working there be happy and helpful!  The food portions are huge and reasonably priced.  Super clean dining room!

data.title: Breakfast with a California flare
data.text: A fellow traveler said we had to eat there while we were at the beach watching waves.Ithe is only a 5 to 10 minute walk up the hill from the beach. A unique 80s pop culture atmosphere with great food. I love eggs Benedict but felt adventurous and tried eggs Flourentine I believe they're called (tomato & spinach added to eggs Benedict). At least once a month I wake up wanting to go here. Fast friendly service.

data.title: Worth a stop in
data.text: We stopped in here on our last day in Oceanside.  It's a cool little 80's themed diner.  Their pancakes are really good, thick and very fluffy.  The bacon was also crispy just like I like it, and the eggs I ordered over medium were perfect; not slimy or too over done.  All in all, a good place I would go back to.

data.title: Very retro indeed!
data.text: Great little informal place for breakfast or lunch. Very open and airy inside, with lots of pictures and a 1980's motif. Wide range of breakfast plates, and sandwiches and burgers. I had an omelet and it came with ribbon cut hash browns (love them) and toast. Everything tasted like it was made with fresh ingredients, and the portions were nice sized. The wait staff were very pleasant and the food was served quite quickly

data.title: Amazing place, Great service, even better food
data.text: My husband and I ate here for the first time a few days after moving to Oceanside. We were pleasantly surprised that even though there was a line of people waiting we only had about a 10 minute wait. The service was better than I could have asked, especially being the Sunday morning rush. I order a Belgian waffle and he order an omelet. The waffle was super thick, fluffy, and amazing taste. It was the entire size of my plate. The omelet was huge as well. My husband actually had leftovers, that never happens. The price of the food for the amount is exceptional. Highly recommend going to this diner.

data.title: Great food, service, owner and theme.
data.text: My husband had a breakfast burrito and he loved it. I had strawberry and whipped cream waffle with sides of eggs and bacon. I always have the fruit etc. served on the side so that the waffle won't get soggy. All was excellent!

data.title: Disappointing....EVERYTHING!
data.text:
The Breakfast Club Diner was on the disappointing side. The wait was very short, but the food took very long to arrive and once it did, it wasn't very pleasing. 
    We took a seat outside for about five to ten minutes until our name was called. At first we were sat by a bathroom, but we requested to change seats. 
   We ordered our drinks, but only one person's arrived and then it took about ten minutes for the rest. I got a hot cocoa and it was adorable and delicious. My parents got a cappuccino. Many pictures showed that the cappuccinos were beautiful and had pretty designs on them. So when they got a plain brown cappuccino they were disappointed. 
   Then later we ordered our food. Most of us ordered pancakes. It took about twenty minutes for us to get our food. Once we got our food the pancakes had an unbearable aftertaste. I couldn't finish my meal. 
   To sum it all all up, I will not be returning to the breakfast club.

data.title: Big portions good food!
data.text: We ate at the Breakfast Club on a Sunday morning. They were quite busy but the service was still fast and the food was really good. We had a couple breakfast burritos and the eggs Benedict (YUM!).

data.title: Delish pancakes!
data.text: Great breakfast treats! I had their veggie omelette with feta, potatoes and a side of pancakes. I'm not a big fan of pancakes, but these were very good! We had to wait a long time for a booth for the four of us...Sunday is probably their busiest day. The Nutella pancakes, with whipped cream and fresh banana was also a delicious treat! You'll enjoy whatever you order! Can't wait to return!

data.title: awesome place!
data.text: This restaurant is the best! The portions are huge and tasty! The décor is great and the owner Perry is very friendly and welcoming! Bring your appetite when you come to this restaurant!

data.title: Huge Pancakes
data.text: The pancakes are huge. The atmosphere is all 80s from the pictures to the music. Family loved it. Happy 4th of July to everyone!

data.title: Egg Skillets to die for!
data.text: Huge portions, great prices, cool vibes with the music. Fast, helpful service and great with kids. Perfect corner location when driving by.

data.title: Giant pancakes, fun decor
data.text: I went here for lunch with a friend. I had the Nutella flapjacks, which were amazing and huge. The the decor was a fun 80s theme, and the service was great! The only downside is that it's a little pricey for breakfast food.

data.title: Awesome food!
data.text: We stopped here on our way to the airport to return home to home to Houston. Best idea ever. Really nice place. The food was great and service was great. The Eggs Benedict had some of the tastiest hollandaise sauce I've had.

data.title: On the way
data.text:
We were trawling San Diego to San Francisco and we found this place from Trip Advisor and perfect landing :)
Very delicious food 
My favorite crazy caprese omlet

data.title: Breakfast
data.text: We went here for breakfast the other weekend. It was steady inside with a few bigger parties dining in. We didn't wait long for a table but it took our server almost 10 minutes to come to the table. She was friendly but not as "on it" as she could have been. The food was average - pricey for breakfast in my opinion.

data.title: Yum! Yum!
data.text: We went there on a Sunday morning while in Oceanside to visit relatives in San Diego. It was a beautiful day, so there as a 45 minute wait. But it was worth every second of it. I had California Skillet which was made with hash brown potatoes, chicken breast, broccoli, cheddar cheese, mushrooms, tomatoes and topped with slices of avocado. It was filling, delicious and reasonably priced!

data.title: Back to the 80s
data.text:
I stopped off for lunch here and found it to be a fascinating 80s themed place. 

There were photos, pictures, guitars etc etc decorating the place, all with an 80s theme, from pictures of the Breakfast Club movie, to a Eddie van Halen guitar, stopping at most points in between.

The service was as one would expect in a diner, and the food was very good from a standard sort of menu for such a place.
